subject: Junit - RMI Interaction (Part II)
msgSnippet: I have found that I am able to use Textui ok, it is just Swingui that interacts with RMI. I suspect that I should somehow change the file excluded.properties
messageBody:
I have found that I am able to use Textui ok, it is just Swingui that
interacts with RMI.

I suspect that I should somehow change the file excluded.properties
in junit.jar (like I had to for using Junit with Log4J) but I don't
know what to edit it to!!!

Steve.
